  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And it was told Solomon,.... By some of his courtiers: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "saying, behold, Adonijah feareth King Solomon; lest he should take away his life: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for, lo, he hath caught hold on the horns of the altar; which was the last resort of the guilty when they despaired of mercy otherwise: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "saying, let King Solomon swear unto me this day that he will not slay his servant with the sword; he owns Solomon to be king, and himself his subject and servant; this no doubt he did to conciliate his favour, nor did he think his life safe, unless Solomon promised with an oath, that he would not take it away. ",
