      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This is one of many passages which show how lightly the Jews esteemed promises in comparison with oaths. The sentiment possibly took its rise in the oaths sworn by the Divine Being (",
        "children": []
